category=Getting Started
description=<p>This example shows you how to store the date and time when a card was last changed--possibly to display the date later, or to sort the cards by last-modification date, or for some other purpose that requires the modification date.</p>
discussion=<p>The <font face="Courier" size="11">closeField</font> message is sent to a field whenever it loses focus after a change to the field's content. When the <font face="Courier" size="11">closeField</font> message is sent to the field, it triggers this handler.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>In this example, the <font face="Courier" size="11">closeField</font> handler should be placed in the stack script. This lets every field on every card update the modification date when the field is changed, without needing to put a copy of the handler in each field's script.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The handler stores the current date and time in a custom property called &quot;lastModDate&quot;. Since the handler specifies that the &quot;lastModDate&quot; custom property will be applied to the current card, this example sets, for each card, the date and time any of its fields was last changed.</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The date and time are stored in the form of <font face="Courier" size="11">the seconds</font> function--the number of seconds since the start of the eon. We store the date and time this way, rather than as a text date and time, for two reasons: because this format doesn't vary depending on the user's system settings, and because it's easy to do arithmetic on (if we want to use a handler to find out whether one date is before or after another).</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>We may want to display the last-modification timestamp to the user. For example, we might put the date and time into a field whenever a card opens. For this purpose, we'll want to <font face="Courier" size="11">convert</font> the <font face="Courier" size="11">seconds</font>--which is simply a number--into something a little more user-friendly. The <font face="Courier" size="11">convert</font> command changes the format of a date:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">on</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> openCard </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#68228B">-- when the user goes to a card</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#68228B">-- grab the custom property:</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">put</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> the lastModDate of the </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">target</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> into myDate</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#68228B">-- switch to a better format:</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">convert</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> myDate from </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">seconds</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> to </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">date</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> and </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#F88017">time</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#68228B">-- display the converted date and time in a field:</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">put</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> myDate into field &quot;Last Mod Date&quot;</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">    </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#0000FF">pass</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> openCard</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier" size="11">  </font><font face="Courier" size="11" color="#980517">end</font><font face="Courier" size="11"> openCard</font></p>
level=2
licensed=false
name=Storing a modification timestamp
solution=<p><font color="#980517">on</font> closeField <font color="#68228B">-- place in card or stack script</font></p>\n<p>  <font color="#0000FF">set</font> the lastModDate of this card to the <font color="#F88017">seconds</font></p>\n<p>  <font color="#0000FF">pass</font> closeField</p>\n<p><font color="#980517">end</font> closeField</p>
title=Storing a modification timestamp